<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezark &amp; Galileo &amp; Santos-Silva, 2016" authorityName="Bezark &amp; Galileo &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2016" box="[324,532,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="swifti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,532,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Stereomerus swifti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[540,632,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[540,632,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from all other species of the genus by the elytral color pattern (see photos at 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezark" box="[328,481,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" refString="Bezark, L. G. (2015) A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the New World. Available from: https: // apps 2. cdfa. ca. gov / publicApps / plant / bycidDB / wsearch. asp? w = n (Accessed September 2015)" type="book chapter" year="2015">Bezark 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Except for 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1994" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1994" box="[640,1142,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachypterous">
<emphasis box="[640,834,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">S. brachypterous</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[847,1142,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1994) Revisao do genero Stereomerus Melzer, 1934 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Desmiphorini). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 39, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1994">Martins &amp; Galileo, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Galileo &amp; Martins, 2003" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1307,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">S. maculatus</emphasis>
Galileo &amp; Martins, 2003
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 2006" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2006" box="[376,783,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[376,492,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">S. hovorei</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo, 2006
</taxonomicName>
(elytral pubescence not forming longitudinal bands), the other species of the genus have distinct longitudinal bands of pubescence on elytra (from base to apex). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[183,481,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1994) Revisao do genero Stereomerus Melzer, 1934 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Desmiphorini). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 39, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1994">Martins &amp; Galileo (1994)</bibRefCitation>
the elytral pubescence in the 
<typeStatus box="[836,934,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1994" box="[978,1171,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachypterous">
<emphasis box="[978,1171,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">S. brachypterous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not well conserved. However the latter differs from the new species by the general color being distinctly lighter. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2006" box="[1205,1435,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[1205,1435,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Stereomerus hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezark &amp; Galileo &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2016" box="[294,385,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="swifti">
<emphasis box="[294,385,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">S. swifti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the slender body (distinctly wider in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2006" box="[849,962,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[849,962,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">S. hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), by the yellowish elytral pubescence not forming a wide, semicircular band on basal third of elytra, and by the yellowish elytral band at the beginning of the distal third not oblique, as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2006" box="[486,599,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei">
<emphasis box="[486,599,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">S. hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2003" box="[615,876,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stereomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[615,876,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Stereomerus maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species mainly by the body being notably slender, the prothorax slender and longer, and with longer antennae (see photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,764,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">holotype</typeStatus>
at Bezark 2016).
</paragraph>
